31/03/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan proposed on Sunday (30 March) that all parties involved in the Cyprus dispute -- Turkey, Greece, the UK and the two communities on the island -- should hold further talks. In an interview with the local press that same day, Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said that a path for finding a solution to the Cyprus problem still exists, reiterating his government's commitment to resolving the problem. (Anadolu Agency, Hurriyet, Milliyet - 30/03/03)
